description: Our journey begins on the title page, as two Victorian children and pet gazelle slip away from their father, treasure map in hand, and embark on an alphabetical path through a sewer populated with every sort of ghoul, only to emerge safe at home at the end. Following the “A is for … ” format, Gaiman’s text takes the form of 13 tight, evocative rhyming couplets, hand-lettered by Grimly. Page turns divide each couplet, moving the action forward and building the sense of mystery. The illustrations do double duty, telling the children’s story and filling each letter’s page with suitably ghastly, nominal matter. There’s some disturbing stuff on display (the sewer walls are lined with children bound in chains, straitjackets, and rusty manacles), but the character of the pictures, spiky and knobby and childlike, and a palette of beiges, accented by muted pastels, mitigates the creepiness. In the end, Gaiman and Grimly have combined forces to produce an acrid, gothic confection that bubbles with vitriol and wit.
name: HC/SC

description:
The biggest event of 2012 is now the biggest miniseries of 2013!

We all know what happened to the Avengers and the X-Men... but what if the story had gone differently?

The one and only Jimmy Palmiotti brings his signature style to a mind-blowing reinterpretation of a key event in the history of the Marvel Universe.

Featuring Magneto, Hope, and every Avenger and X-Man you can imagine!

description: BATTLE ROYALE! John Cartney couldn't beat the future, so instead he's using the future to beat the life out of John Steed and Emma Peel. The super-spies face their deadliest adversaries, The Cybernauts!
name: Punchlines and Proposals

description: The BEING has been freed from his eternal prison and the Grimm Universe trembles in fear. As The Being journey's with Samira to find the one person that resides in the dark dimension who holds the key to his release from the shadowlands, Sela and the Hunters finds themselves face to face against of colony of demons intent on freeing one of their own even if it means tearing our wayward heroes apart. Don't miss out on the prequel to the Grimm Universe event series of the year by the Wonderland and Fly writer, Raven Gregory. - Unleashed tie-in!

volume.name: Grimm Fairy Tales presents Hunters: The Shadowlands

description: Dragged back into the Realm of Myst against her will, Robyn finds herself fighting the mysterious assassin, Avella. As Gisbourne watches from afar, putting all of the pieces into place for his endgame, the citizens of Nottingham are left at the mercy of the monstrous Dark Horde. Robyn must return to the people she once liberated to lead their rebellion... but will she survive Avella's wrath long enough to do so?

volume.name: Grimm Fairy Tales presents Robyn Hood: Wanted

description: Since 1988, PREVIEWS has been your ultimate source for all of the comics and merchandise to be available from your local comic book shop... revealed up to two months in advance! Hundreds of comics and graphic novels from the best comic publishers; the coolest pop-culture merchandise on Earth; plus PREVIEWS exclusive items available nowhere else! Now more than ever, PREVIEWS is there to show the tales, toys and treasures in your future! This August issue features items scheduled to ship in October 2013 and beyond.

WIth EXCLUSIVE DIGITAL CONTENT including original art and sketches!

A World War II hero is empowered to fight in the eternal war between Heaven and Hell!

This issue, Blazing Glory's supernatural ODYSSEY continues, as John Wilson ends up on the front line -- in arm's reach of ADOLPH HITLER!

The camping where the family Kiekeboe stays, seems to be no ordinary camping. First of all, Kiekeboe meets almost only people he knows. Second, he gets seducted by the beautiful Mona. Third, Mikal, the shy new friend of Fanny, lives there with his grandpa-vampire. Most of all there's a hospital nearby where fake white blood is made.
name: Het Witte Bloed

description: Digital First!!! An all-new Miss Fury adventure never before seen in print! Miss Fury is back in time again! Or is she? Will Miss Fury be able to make it home for a nice long bath, or will she forever be transported? Find out now! Part 1 of 3.

The final battle for Earth will decide the fate of not only all magical beings-but also mankind as well! The powerful Kon and his collective group of magical entities wage war on Orlana and her thundering army, as they must defeat the Death Princess at all costs, or risk losing everything!
name: Into the Void

description: Jeanne Darm is promoted from toilet cleaning lady to president of the republic Paranoia. The sodagiant Dromedaris supports her policy in return for cornering the market segment. Fanny is modelling for the posters of Dromedaris while Charlotte works as interim at the rival Kameel. This, ofcourse, causes complications.
name: Jeanne Darm

description: Thanks to genetic manipulation of plants, professor Noël Joyeux has developed seeds out of which grow christmas trees complete with balls. But this invention is merely a cover to export christmas trees filled with heroin. Kiekeboe lands in prison and Fanny in a strip joint.
name: Prettige Feestdagen

description: Thanks to a mistaken identity, Fanny is taken up in the harem of Fes. Luckily Moemoe and Konstantinopel are also in Marocco. Meanwhile Kiekeboe argues with a tax inspector.
name: De Fez Van Fes

description: On the Côte Anyeau in France there are attacks on a few well known restaurants. Marcel Kiekeboe discovers that the famous author Lambert Saint Val escapes death every time at the attacks. Fanny forces herself into Villa Delfia, the home of Saint Val. She gets discovered by the dangerous gangster Sam Etégal.
name: Villa Delfia

description: Because of her low pension, Moemoe decides to set up a gang to steal fur coats. At that same moment Fanny and her new friend Aart Appel have a campaign against wearing fur. The whole thing escalates and ends in court, with a heart warming plea of Moemoe.
name: De Bende Van Moemoe

description: Fanny is on the trail of a swindel in hormone preparations for body builders. Meanwhile, Kiekeboe is treated with a hormone spray and that treatment has a peculiar effect. Throughout the comic there are some commercials that get out of hand too.
name: De Spray-Historie

description:
By accident, the family Kiekeboe stays at a haunted castle. A murder is committed there recently. Monsters, ghouls, murdering heirs and fear dominates the family until they hear they have witnessed an organized ghostweekend.

After the main story there is a short story titled Arsène Lupin and the Stradivarius. In it, a trumpet gets stolen from Goegebuer. It is found by Fanny and Arsène Lupin.
name: De Spookfirma

description: Fanny has a job as a working student at the new Hotel "O" on the French island Île Faux le Fer. The hotel guests don't always seem to be who they claim to be. When the other members of the Kiekeboe family also arrive at the Hotel "O", the thieves must be on their guard.
name: Hotel "O"

description: On Antartica, a frozen Napoleon is thawed by the Bonaparte-committee, to make him a new world leader. But soon problems arise. Napoleon doesn't know he used to be emperor and Kiekeboe discovers a complot.
name: Een Koud Kunstje

description:
For AFTERLIFE INC. - Proud Purveyors of a Premium Paradise - taking control of a newly-modernised afterlife was the easy part. Keeping it is another matter entirely. And when the stakes are this high, it's more than just their necks on the line... it's their jobs too!

From sinister councils and military incursions, to mad kings, rocket dogs and unspeakable horror, it's all in a day's work for CEO Jack Fortune and his ragtag band of corporate go-getters. Life may be over but the future is only just beginning.

Collecting the hit series NEAR LIFE and DEAD DAYS - plus a wealth of additional stories, special features and exclusive print-only material - NEAR LIFE AND OTHER STORIES marks the triumphant return to the world of AFTERLIFE INC. as written by Jon Lock and illustrated by a stunning selection of artists.
name: Near Life and Other Stories

description:
"Is that a light at the end of the tunnel... or the gunpowder flash inside a DOUBLE BARREL!?

In Zander's HECK, our hero sets out to get his best friend back... even if it kills him! It's a titanic battle that'll blow your mind and break your heart. Then, in Kevin's CRATER XV, Captain Sztab risks everything for a chance of reaching space, while the real astronauts are having second thoughts... and Army's beloved Pravda may be hiding a dark secret! Meanwhile, Tim Sievert's CLANDESTINAUTS face giant lizards and double wizards! Plus Zander explains why you don't want your characters to be like Bruce Wayne, and more... Hey, the intro comic alone is worth the price of admission, just to see Kevin and Zander with handlebar mustaches!"
name: Heck; Crater XV; The Clandestinauts

description: Enter issues 51 to 75 of the Grimm Unvierse, a place where fairy tales are real and the nightmares never end! Follow Sela as she continues her search for truth and justice through the four realms of power -- all while protecting the Nexus from the constant threat of danger! Decisions are made and lives are changes forever. With the forces of good and the forces of evil constantly at odds, the story continues in the third installment of this omnibus series. Don't miss a second of the action and collect the third volume today!
name: Volume 3

description: Antimony receives a phone call from her father and the converstation turns out to be a coded message only a friend from her father's past can decode.
name: Microsat 5

description: Welcome back to a world where the rich can afford the best in super hero protection, but the poor have to get by with the heroic equivalent of third party, fire and theft. Who the heck is Blue Girl and isn't it a bit late to be introducing new characters anyway? This is it, at last, we find out just who Quietus is and what he wants, and, really, it's not nice. You won't like it. Also, vampires! Which are vastly over used in popular media, but, hey, vampires! Who doesn't like vampires, eh? In a world where being a super hero is just another job, what happens when there's nobody left alive to pay the bill? Quietus -- some men just want to watch the world die.
name: Quietus

description:
A beloved Lenore character must die -- forever!!!

That's right: one of your beloved undead is going to reach the end of their improbably-animated rope... and be removed from the afterlife for all eternity! Meanwhile, Lenore terrorises a ghost-hunting TV show -- and the origin of Taxidermy is finally revealed!

Note: The digital edition (7/24/2013) for this issue was released early.

From the Shuster award winning creators of Least I Could Do and Gutters comes a loving nod to classic fantasy novels that manages to flip the genre on it's head. Unlikely heros cut a swath through a fantasy world that is extremely familiar and yet very different. A naive elven hunter makes an strange friend in an undead warlock and the two manage to make both enemies and friends as they fight the good fight against the Legaran Empire.

Based on a property by Mike Krahulik and Jerry Holkins, the creative minds behind the wildly popular Penny Arcade webcomic. In this exciting issue, the Lookouts confrontation with the Sphinx reaches its peak and we learn about Eli's true abilities.
